I went to visit my friend Sophia over the past Lady-Day week-end in London. I wanted to visit her for a longer time but hurry in Easter break has one down side. They don't allow two-on-one meetings so actually I had to spend two-on-one meeting times with my family and my dogs so my friend and her dogs could be spent time all together. Maybe we should have called it "one-on-one meetings meetings meeting"???

On the day of Easter, the island was filled with kids and toursim. People want to escape the cold and lonely city. I wanted to escape the heat and loneliness.

You might ask why didn't I go to a more remote island, like Isle of Man, or the Faroe Islands? For that you need to buy plane tickets!!! So the not-so-cheap fares to the UK are really only in very convenient periods for me (and my family).
